---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Inclusion criteria"
  description="The published criteria a tool must meet to be included in the fabricstack catalog."
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl prose prose-zinc dark:prose-invert">
    <h1>Inclusion criteria</h1>
    <p>
      fabricstack does not rank, rate, or recommend. Inclusion is curated
      against these published criteria: tools that meet them are in; tools that
      don't, aren't.
    </p>

    <h2>A tool must</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>
        Be specifically built for, or directly useful to, Microsoft Fabric
        and/or Power BI development.
      </li>
      <li>
        Be publicly accessible: not internal-only, and not behind a private
        NDA or agreement.
      </li>
      <li>
        Be a <strong>tool</strong>: a CLI, SDK, API, MCP server, library,
        framework, IDE extension, desktop app, web app, template, or hosted
        service. <strong>Not</strong> a blog post, course, book, video,
        tutorial, or other learning material.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2>What is not required</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Documentation is not required.</li>
      <li>
        Active maintenance is not required; deprecated tools stay in the
        catalog, marked with a badge.
      </li>
      <li>A free tier is not required.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Review</h2>
    <p>
      The site maintainer reviews each submission and either approves it (a pull
      request is merged) or declines it (the issue is closed with a comment
      referencing the criterion that wasn't met).
    </p>

    <p class="not-prose mt-8">
      <a
        href="/submit"
        class="inline-flex rounded-md bg-accent px-5 py-2.5 text-sm font-medium text-accent-contrast hover:opacity-90"
      >
        Submit a tool →
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
